## 🔵 Step 1: Forward Pass (Normal Kadane)

```python
    for i in range(1, n):
        forward[i] = max(arr[i], forward[i-1] + arr[i])
```

Meaning:
At each index, decide:

* Start new subarray from `arr[i]`
* OR extend previous subarray

Formula:

```
forward[i] = max(current element,
                 previous sum + current element)
```

For `[1,-2,0,3]`:

| i | forward |
| - | ------- |
| 0 | 1       |
| 1 | -1      |
| 2 | 0       |
| 3 | 3       |

---

## 🔵 Step 2: Backward Pass (Reverse Kadane)

```python
    for i in range(n-2, -1, -1):
        backward[i] = max(arr[i], backward[i+1] + arr[i])
```

Same logic but from right to left.

For `[1,-2,0,3]`:

| i | backward |
| - | -------- |
| 3 | 3        |
| 2 | 3        |
| 1 | 1        |
| 0 | 2        |

